  "commentary": "With SPX at 6978.35 sitting just below the massive 7000 gamma wall (14.8B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above 7000 as they're long gamma in PIN regime. The GEX surge event combined with spot trading 98 points above the flip at 6880 creates a strong mean-reverting environment where dealers will fade directional moves. Key resistance cluster at 7000-7025-7050 should act as a ceiling, while any dip toward 6880 flip or 6800 max negative gamma would trigger dealer buying.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get capped near 7000 with pullback pressure toward 6900-6920.",
